3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:11,000
Pure hatred, their Mephisto's army.

4
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:15,000
We wanted them to feel a little bit more different from your typical demon family.

5
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:16,000
Everyone's quality was top notch.

6
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:19,000
But at the time, we didn't know if it was going to work.

7
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:22,000
I think what we landed is going to turn some heads.

8
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:27,000
This is not your normal thing. It's the living form of hatred.

9
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:39,000
The new monster class that we get to introduce, they're called hollows.

10
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:42,000
These hollows have actually been around for like millennia.

11
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:48,000
Mephisto at some point did go to Nahantu a long, long, long time ago.

12
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:53,000
And these hollows were a reaction of Mephisto being in Nahantu at the time.

13
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:55,000
And then they went dormant.

14
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Bringing Mephisto in the Soul Stone seems like the right thing to do for Narell.

15
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:09,000
But it has a chain reaction that I don't think anybody was prepared for.

16
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:17,000
The hollows are really rife throughout Nahantu now that Mephisto is back.

17
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:20,000
And just visually, like horribly disgusting.

18
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:25,000
And sort of made up of the things that have been consumed by the hollows.

19
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Yeah, they're an extension of evil.

20
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:33,000
Infecting wildlife and other monsters and people with this thing called ichor.

21
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:37,000
And they're just sort of going mad.

22
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:48,000
When we're designing the hollows, the main thing that we wanted to push was just if hatred came to life, what would it look like?

23
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:57,000
So we're thinking this black goo that's kind of like formless but also have this red anger energy inside of it.

24
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:02,000
And then with concept, we just want to make, you know, cool monsters.

25
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:06,000
What if it's three legs? What if it's no legs? What if it has like three arms?

26
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:10,000
So we pushed a lot of like options and exploration.

27
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:15,000
And then from then on, like everyone from narrative to design and concept would talk about it.

28
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:19,000
It's like, okay, we like this one and then we can push it and move it further.

29
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:24,000
The hollow family is made up of four members.

30
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:29,000
The swarmer, the spitter, the caster, and the brutes.

31
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:36,000
A big thing for me was that the family need to be overwhelming without just relying on pure numbers.

32
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:41,000
So they're going to get stronger over time if you let them fester their hatred after all.

33
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:46,000
The swarmer can teleport and attack you from behind, from the sides.

34
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:49,000
The spitter is a slug with legs.

35
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:54,000
They spew out this vomit stream of who the brute is.

36
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:56,000
The big hulking slow guy of the family.

37
00:02:56,000 --> 00:03:00,000
He has the shield that's buffing and making the rest of the army stronger.

38
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:04,000
The caster is responsible for creating new swarmers.

39
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:09,000
They also will channel onto a specific hollow and view them with an extra feature.

40
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:11,000
It makes them stronger and more deadly.

41
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:18,000
The hollow caster's role serve as an elegant, hovering, yet menacing dungeon character in the game.

42
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:22,000
Really inform many of our design ideas.

43
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:31,000
When we want to make a new variant, we want to know in which specific area we are going to see that character or creature.

44
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:34,000
Readability is like the main focus.

45
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:40,000
We went through several iterations on the design, the texture, the materials, and the camera testing.

46
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:44,000
The day after she gave me like, what was it, 10 different variations?

47
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,000
Different variations?

48
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,000
Okay.

49
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:47,000
Now we are talking.

50
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:58,000
The emission on the spikes really like, did an awesome job to both on the CineVet and also to improve the readability.

51
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:03,000
And in the end, we have the version that we were both happy with.

52
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:07,000
And yeah, hand it over to the tech artist.

53
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:15,000
We had some really strong narrative direction in understanding how big of a role hatred played.

54
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:20,000
And we knew that we needed one look to tie it all together.

55
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:23,000
This hatred has one source and it's all about Mephisto.

56
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:32,000
For the hollows specifically, we identified that we wanted to do some special work with the materials, with the shaders for those characters.

57
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:45,000
Shaders are the code that runs on the GPU that takes in all sorts of inputs like textures and lighting and position and outputs what the object's surface is supposed to look like.

58
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:57,000
We wanted a shader that was capable of adding this sludge layer, this hatred layer over top of it, and making it dynamic and animating so that it really looks like it was constantly undulating or writhing.

59
00:04:57,000 --> 00:05:07,000
So once we had this shader function, we were able to apply that in all these different contexts, like the monsters, like the environment, the character armors even.

60
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:15,000
Most of the shader work was done by Alex, who really took that shader function and made it work in all sorts of different contexts.

61
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:29,000
And we also have the hatred add-ons to these characters, these tentacles, these writhing hatred growths all over them, which was a procedurally generated process that was largely run by Sky on our team.

62
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:37,000
The Hollows boss was kind of born of this idea of what does a pinnacle hollows really look like.

63
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:44,000
We have the Hollows family, and that was pretty well defined by the time that the Hollows boss kind of came up for concepting.

64
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:54,000
Our artist, Victor, had a lot of cool ideas for horror themes and really wanted to push visuals with contortions and breaking the neck of this monster all over the place.

65
00:05:54,000 --> 00:06:02,000
That's where we had the option to go, like, and we'd push it and really get that idea of what Hatred and the Hollows are all about.

66
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:09,000
This inky black ichor that latched on to a once powerful spellcaster.

67
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:17,000
It was such a great source of power that this particular Hollows monster turned into the priestess of Hatred.

68
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:24,000
I'm Victor Lee, a principal concept artist on the Diablo team.

69
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:39,000
and I concepted the Priestess of Hatred.

70
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:49,000
Victor Lee is one of the OGs from Diablo and he's known for creating a lot of dark imagery.

71
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:56,000
And every time we want to have a monster or boss, he's done all the greats, even Diablo himself.

72
00:06:56,000 --> 00:07:03,000
One of his monitors on the side of his desk is just like a dark black eye staring at him.

73
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:10,000
And so when we needed something that's pure darkness, like, we had to tap Vic.

74
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:18,000
I feel like when we're talking about Hatred, I kind of imagine, visualize it as like a black webby-like thing.

75
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:23,000
So I thought a spider configuration would work for this.

76
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:30,000
So I did a few variations, some with souls, human souls trapped in the abdomen.

77
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:34,000
It's like a purgatory because this creature consumes humans.

78
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:40,000
I have this nagging feeling for a long time that why I felt it's not working.

79
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,000
It's not working.

80
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:47,000
No matter how interesting the design is, I'm not pushing the boundaries.

81
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:51,000
So I basically rethought the whole thing.

82
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:56,000
A lot of our creatures are just like raw aggression.

83
00:07:56,000 --> 00:08:00,000
It's just muscly and just brutal.

84
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:02,000
Maybe this one is more insidious.

85
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:08,000
What if the human figure is not controlling the hatred, but it's the other way around?

86
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:13,000
Like the hatred is actually mocking humanity.

87
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:16,000
It's like dragging a puppet around.

88
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:29,000
So what I did is I kept the human figure as a focal point, but the rest of the creature is this moving mass of basically a ball of hatred.

89
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:35,000
It broke a lot of rules, but I felt, I just felt like this just fits.

90
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:46,000
So I went ahead with it and rendered it out.

91
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:51,000
